data.name: Label31.Text
data.value: Note : Offsets (G55) are automatically down loaded when a GCode program is started, and are only in effect while the program is running. All other times (G54) offsets are active, which are all set to zero.

data.name: Label36.Text
data.value: The above information is for the last tool measurement done. The 'Total Offset 'column of boxes above are the offsets used when running a GCode program. A tool measurement can be made by clicking the 'Measure Tool' button on the main form, or one of the three buttons at the top of the Toolsetter tab. The three buttons at the top of the Toolsetter tab will set the appropriate radio buttons above that show the measuremet type. The 'Measure Tool' button on the main form uses the Measurement Type specifed in the Operition (See build tab).
